<TEXT>
the colorado democratic party on sunday disavowed 
a congressional candidate who it said failed to respond to 
allegations in a lawsuit that he distributed posters connecting an 
airline with aids 
the executive committee of the state party voted 331 to deny 
john j mitchell the use of the name democrat in his house campaign 
the party needed to deal with this openly dont flinch dont 
blush just do business and i think thats what weve done here 
said state democratic chairman buie seawell 
trans world airlines has accused mitchell of distributing 
anonymous posters with such messages as aids is spread through 
twa and twa travel with aids 
according to twas lawsuit which seeks 500000 in damages 
mitchell sent a poster to the airlines new york offices in july 
saying thousands of these have been sent around the country our 
staff is working on a new poster they will continue to be sent 
until twa corrects the hurt you have causedcost me 
mitchells squabble with twa apparently began in 1983 when he 
took the airline to small claims court in two separate cases to 
recover frequent flyer benefits he felt he deserved mitchell 
won one case and lost another 
mitchell did not attend sundays meeting state party leaders 
said he has not made himself available to talk with them about the 
matter since the lawsuit was filed sept 19 in us district court 
at denver 
the 53yearold teacher and realtor from colorado springs 
reportedly has denied the charges made by twa he did not respond 
to messages including one sunday night left by the associated 
press on his home phone answering machine 
in his first foray into politics mitchell was unopposed for the 
democratic nomination to run against republican rep joel hefley in 
the heavily republican 5th congressional district which 
encompasses colorado springs 
the district democratic committee met first sunday and issued a 
complaint saying mitchells failure to respond to the controversy 
surrounding the lawsuit has hurt the campaigns of other democratic 
candidates in the district 
i can verify that it is hurting my candidacy people ask me 
what craziness are you going to come up with said ray james 
who is running against an incumbent republican for a legislative 
seat in the district 
the partys vote sunday wont affect the ballot which already 
has been printed but the party said it would publish the disavowal 
in newspapers 
rick daily the partys attorney stressed that the party wasnt 
making a judgment on twas allegations against mitchell but was 
moving against him only because of mr mitchells failure to act 
like a responsible candidate and step forward and deal with those 
issues 
seawell called mitchell a walkon candidate and said he was 
nominated with the best of intentions 
he was a realtor an educator and seemed like a nice guy 
the party chairman said 
mitchell teaches communications at pikes peak community college 
