a lifesized bronze statue of 
elvis presley was unloaded in bremerhaven port saturday exactly 30 
years after the reallife rocknroll idol came down the gangplank 
here as a us army soldier 
the statue brought from london to commemorate preselys arrival 
oct 1 1958 was hoisted off the ship helgoland by a crane as 
performer dirk juettner of west berlin sang presley hits including 
wooden heart and love me tender 
while juettner imitated presleys hipjerking style a crowd of 
about 300 gathered to watch the ceremony which included a 
rocknroll dance group performance on the dock in this northern 
port city 
after the arrival ceremony the statue was taken by a convoy of 
vehicles with organizers and fans to bad neuheim 225 miles south 
where it was to remain on display for 24 hours presley lived in 
bad neuheim during his 17 months as a us soldier in west germany 
the statue was sent to bremerhaven for the commemoration by the 
elvis presley center of london where it was to be returned after a 
oneday stay in west germany the center said in a statement 
released to the news media 
presley was born jan 8 1935 in tupelo miss he was 42 when he 
died in memphis tenn on aug 16 1977 
