of bavaria about 65 miles northeast of munich 
schwaabe told the associated press in a telephone interview from 
his office in munich that strauss was conscious and his condition 
had stabilized by late saturday evening doctors were planning to 
operate to correct strauss condition schwaabe said 
however the statement issued early sunday superseded the 
earlier statements indicating strauss had taken a turn for the 
worse 
the outspoken strauss often has been at the center of national 
policymaking and has used international travels to wield influence 
over foreign policy as well 
his thick bavarian accent coupled with stinging comments also 
makes the outspoken corpulent state governor west germanys most 
colorful politician 
from 1966 to 1969 strauss served as finance minister under 
thenchancellor kurt georg kiesinger in the socalled great 
coalition of west germanys conservative parties with the 
leftleaning social democrats 
after the social democrats took over the government in coalition 
with the centrist businessoriented free democratic party in 1969 
strauss remained as a member of the federal parliaments 
conservative opposition until 1978 when he was elected governor of 
bavaria 
two years later he was nominated to run for chancellor but lost 
the election against social democrat helmut schmidt in 1980 he 
kept his post as bavarian state governor 
